# API — copy to apps/api/.env and fill secrets (local daily dev).
# Cloud stg/prd: Doppler project `api` → Railway Sync. See infra/doppler/README.md.
# Public URLs, CORS, and AUTH_COOKIE_DOMAIN derive from APP_ENV + DEPLOY_PLATFORM.

# Local Postgres: `docker compose up -d db` (see repo-root compose.yaml).
# The app only needs DATABASE_URL — no other DB env vars.
# Cloud: set to managed/Railway/Coolify Postgres URL with `?sslmode=require`.

#

## secrets
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:password@localhost:5432/postgres
BETTER_AUTH_SECRET=f8a3fbd829c78c656be46817a8e4226a170ec80251ef004a4e3a81e11f5225f4

## runtime
PORT=5000
APP_ENV=dev
DEPLOY_PLATFORM=local
NODE_ENV=development

## optional
### transactional email (Resend)
RESEND_API_KEY=

### override derived cookie domain (default: .{local-base} local, .{cloud-base} cloud — see product.ts)
# AUTH_COOKIE_DOMAIN=.userepro.test
